<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n08138a"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n08" href="#n08138a">N08 (VI.B.6)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n08all.htm#n08138a"> 138(a)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Fr. Le Roux Rouvi&egrave;re / murdered by Eskimos / found wearing soutane &amp; / vestments</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><b>By the Way <font color="green">[&hellip;]</font> Law in the Arctic</b> <br> It was from Edmonton the Canadian Police started in 1915 to investigate what proved to be the <mark>murder of</mark> two Oblate Fathers&mdash;<mark>Father Rouviere</mark>, who has given his name to a lake in the Far North, and <mark>Father William Le Roux</mark>. They had travelled up the Mackenzie River, and away to the mouth of the Coppermine River, to bring tidings of the Gospel to the Esquimaux. For two years nothing was heard of them. Then an explorer met some <mark>Eskimos wearing soutanes and vestments</mark>, and the alarm was given. <small> <a name="FJ8feb24" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#FJ8feb24"><cite title="source">Freeman's Journal</cite></a> (8 February 1924) 8/8</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Note: line joining &lsquo;Eskimos&rsquo; to &lsquo;soutane&rsquo;. </mm> </dd></dl>
